                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#0v" facs="001"/><desc> Drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> (Walatta Ṗeṭros?) with arms upraised</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#5r" facs="005"/><desc>Drawing of horse, raised up on hindquarters, wearing a bridle</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#32v" facs="033"/><desc>Illumination of ʾabuna Batra Māryām (background) before the depiction of a church in a grove of trees (foreground), with two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref>s (labeled as Mik[āʾel] and Ga[brǝʾel]) hovering above</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#50r" facs="050"/><desc>Drawing of figure (Walatta Ṗeṭros?) on hands and knees and weeping</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#57r" facs="057"/><desc>Harag at head of new section, with talismanic symbols (eyes)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#62r" facs="062"/><desc>Geometric patterns <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1109GeometricPatterns"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1109GeometricPatterns</span></ref> as section divider (harag)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#74r" facs="074"/><desc>Drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with two guardian <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>s, left and right</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#93r" facs="093"/><desc>Seated figure left (Walatta Ṗeṭros?) and <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> right (<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName>?) pointing at the drawing of a church.  An <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/> hovers above and to the left. The face of the seated figure has been painted. Below is the first word of a caption <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ</foreign></q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#94v" facs="095"/><desc>Drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> (Walatta Ṗeṭros?) with arms upraised</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#98v" facs="099"/><desc>Talismanic symbol, as section divider, in black and red ink</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#101r" facs="101"> f. 101r, colum 2</locus><desc>Drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> (Walatta Ṗeṭros?) bowing on hands and knees</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#103r" facs="103"/><desc>Walatta Ṗeṭros, with upraised hands with caption <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡</foreign></q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d13"><locus target="#106r" facs="106"> f. 106r, column 2</locus><desc>Drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> seated on a throne (left), with a woman with upraised hands (Walatta Ṗeṭros?) before him (right), and a saint, prostrate below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d14"><locus target="#107v" facs="108"/><desc>Crude drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with Drawn <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and two other figures (<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>?), in red and black ink</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#0v #107r" facs="001 107"/>
                    <desc>
                    The digitization of the book was only partial.  There are clearly visible in the first image, many folios before the first one digitized.  Likewise, there are clearly visible in the last image, many folios after the last one digitized
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#4v" facs="005"/>
                    <desc type="Record">
                    Record, church land transaction, with judges and witnesses, written in a different hand, mostly effaced
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#5r" facs="005"/>
                    <desc type="Record">
                    Record, church land transaction, with judges and witnesses, written in a different hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#32v" facs="033"/>
                    <desc type="Record">
                    Record, church land transaction, with judges and witnesses, written in a different hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#38r" facs="038"/>
                    <desc>
                    Record, church land transaction, with judges and witnesses, written in a different hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#4v" facs="005"/>
                    <desc>
                      “Our Holy mother Walatta Ṗeṭros, died in her 40th year, in the year 7,165 on the 11th epact and the 19th Matqa [Jewish New Year, lit. Shofar, which is taken to be the analogue of the bell in Christian culture], in the fifth year of the reign of our emperor Yohannes, lover of God in the year of Matthew, the evangelist. We wrote this book of gadl because of a spirit of jealousy arose about our holy mother, Walatta Ṗeṭros, to be read on the 17th of Ḫǝdār.” The owner is mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብራ፡ ያዕቆብ፡</foreign>, Gabrā Yāʿqob, also mentioned 35v, and 93r (where the wife is mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሜልኮል፡</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    Digitized by Wendy Laura Belcher with Selamawit Mecca in January 2011 with a Canon Powershot outdoors at the Bäträ Maryam Monastery on Zāge pennisula in lake Ṭānā
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
